FBI agents are coordinating updates regarding the Epstein case. The VC squad has no planned activity for today, and VCAC is being asked to confirm they have no planned activity. Updates are being relayed between FBI units, including NY and MIMM, concerning file transfers from FBINET to UNET.

*   CID requests a 1530 daily phone call with NY for updates. *   NY proposes end-of-day reporting Monday-Friday, with weekend updates only occurring due to significant events. *   There’s discussion about consolidating reporting from VCAC, VC, and CR units, with CID potentially taking the lead. *   The VC squad has no planned updates for the Epstein case this weekend. *   The email chain includes requests for confirmation and CCing of communications. Note: Significant portions of the text have been redacted.

On August 25, 2019, FBI agents in NY and CID discussed reporting procedures for the EFTA00037560 case.  NY planned to have end-of-day reporting Monday-Friday. PM was designated as the CID point of contact (POC) to minimize disruptions.  Updates were to be consolidated through CID, initially with ICVCU receiving a break. The VC squad and VCAC had no planned updates for that day (August 25th). A file transfer named FBINET to UNET was discussed, with NY directing the VC squad to not have any updates planned for the weekend.

Emails between FBI agents (identified as “NY” and “CID”) discuss updates regarding the FBINET to UNET file uploads and reporting related to the Epstein case.  VC Squad and VCAC have no planned activity for the weekend. CID is coordinating consolidation of reporting from VCAC, VC, and CR through “M.”  Updates are being sent to multiple individuals, including ICVCU.

An email chain discusses the lack of planned updates for the Epstein case by the VC Squad and VCAC. The CID (FBI) is inquiring about consolidation efforts, specifically whether they are being handled through the VC side or by the individual CID agent.  NY (FBI) has confirmed no updates are planned for the weekend. Files related to “FBINET to UNET Uploaded Files” were being shared. EFTA00037570 and EFTA00037571 are identified as file references.

On August 25, 2019, an FBI CID agent (NY) communicated with another FBI CID agent regarding the Epstein case investigation. The plan was for daily reporting (Monday-Friday) and a shift away from weekend work, contingent on significant events. Updates were to be consolidated from VCAC, VC, and CR teams. On August 24, 2019, the VC squad reported no planned updates for the weekend related to the Epstein case, and a request was made to confirm the same for VCAC.  EFTA00037568 and EFTA00037569 are file references.

On August 25, 2019, CID (FBI) requested a daily 1530 phone call with NY (FBI) for updates on the Epstein case. NY agreed to end-of-day reporting Monday-Friday, anticipating a return to normal investigative patterns. CID requested a point of contact (POC) and continued updates. The VC Squad had no planned updates for the weekend. There were discussions about consolidating reporting from VCAC, VC, and CR.  A file transfer (FBINET to UNET) was referenced, and updates were communicated regarding the VC Squad's lack of planned activity.

*   CID requested a 1530 daily phone call with NY for updates on EFTA00037562. *   NY agreed to end-of-day reporting Mon-Fri, with weekend updates only occurring due to significant events. *   CID requested that updates be sent to them and a designated point of contact (POC). *   The VC squad had no planned updates for the Epstein case on August 25, 2019. *   VCAC was asked to confirm if they also had no planned updates. *   The FBI discussed file uploads between FBINET and UNET. *   EFTA00037563 was referenced.
